 New Haven Superior Court Judge Thomas O'Keefe Jr. ruled Monday that 49-year-old Lishan Wang should be sent to Connecticut Valley Hospital for treatment .
In a court report , mental health experts said Wang displayed ` paranoid thinking and was ` guarded and suspicious ' when discussing a relationship with court-appointed lawyers .
Wang is charged with murder in the shooting of Dr. Vajinder Toor outside his home in April 2010 .